{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01Tg4RCdBFwY4zrqmPQhQpDr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The configuration works as required.\n\n**Results:**\n- **`/api`**: Under a 20-request burst, the first few requests return `200` (allowed rate + small burst across the 3 controller pods), and all excess requests return `429`. ✅\n- **`/health`**: All 20 requests return `200` — it remains completely unlimited. ✅\n\n**What I did** — added two annotations to the `rate-api` Ingress only (leaving `rate-health` and the application Deployment untouched):\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \"1\"` — effective ~1 request/second.\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: \"1\"` — keeps the burst allowance tight so excess requests promptly get `429` rather than a large free burst.\n\nBecause the limit is enforced per controller pod and there are 3 replicas, the burst-multiplier was reduced to keep the effective rate close to 1 rps. The success criteria are met: `/api` returns `429` for excess requests while `/health` stays `200` under load."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":889,"cache_read_input_tokens":33679,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":889},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"65b8e0cf-1f22-4037-8a45-77618e3e561e","uuid":"adcc1991-9df8-4c98-bc0d-2a56fc4ecb56","request_id":"req_011CcAWX5JRZa39GgE5NW7kj"}
